    section.two
      .content
        h1 Call for papers
        p.lead We are planning Knowit's yearly company-wide software developer conference! It will be held on the 13th - 14th of November 2015 in Stockholm, Sweden. The last day for submitting a talk is August 20th, 2015.
        p.important We are seeking motivated developers to speak at the conference about topics such as:
        dl.dl-horizontal
          dt Architecture
          dd Microservices, DDD, containere (Docker, Rocket...), event-sourcing, asynchronous services, fault tolerant systems, REST, dependency injection, web services without frameworks, web services without app servers, in-memory computing
          dt Mobile
          dd Mobile first design, testing tools, multi-platform development, Apple Watch, iOS, Android, Windows Mobile
          dt Devops
          dd Infrastructure as code, provisioning, continuous deployment
          dt Persistence
          dd NoSQL, SQL, big data, cloud, grid
          dt Web
          dd *.js, responsive design, HTML5, Less/Sass
          dt Test code
          dd Writing good tests, testing tools, continuous testing, TDD, BDD
          dt Programming
          dd Paradigms, parallelism, typing, languages (C#, F#, Scala, Elixir, Clojure, etc.)
          dt Tools
          dd Version control, build systems, SaaS, analysis (Sonar, R, etc.)
          dt Platforms and other
          dd Cloud, Internet of Things, CMS, CRM, Office 365, EPiServer
        p.subtext ... and more!
        p
          | Your audience? Passionate and truly interested developers within the Knowit organization, mainly
          | programming on the Java and .NET platforms for the web.
        h3 Register today! Registration closes on ../..-2015
        p
          a.btn(href='https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1Jx2Op9btb-3wh_zswwp5Ti9HFDVAb9wWiTqI4mj_AzM/viewform' target='_blank')
            | Register here!
        h3 Bla
        p: em
          | We are open to suggestion on workshops, full presentations (60 min), shorter presentations (30 min), and lightning
          | talks (10 min).
        p
          | We are interested in talks and contributions that will captivate and inspire the
          | participants!
        p
          | More information about the venue, registration and other practicalities will be announced later.
          | If you have any questions contact us at <a href="mailto:kds@knowit.no">kds@knowit.no</a>.
        p
          a.btn(href='https://docs.google.com/forms/d/13bf7QFAFAMBqsebA2GNf2v4moLLK_6bmvywutFBY6Qw/viewform?usp=send_form' target='_blank')
            | Submit your presentation

